stylometry: As a manager, you want some lines, in order for business to keep flowing, to limit the downtime, which is money and time wasted.  However, one tradeoff is the possiblity for burnout, you can't expenct 100% effiicency, because people need breaks.  But like I said, you don't want too much downtime, as you are still paying employees, and paying for space and inventory and equipment, that is standing idle, not earning money, which means it is losing money.  Too long of lines, can cause the the company to lose business when people tire of waiting in lines and decide to take their business elsewhere.
